# CODEOWNERS — Golden Path TWO-TIER review routing (template).
#
# Model: AUTONOMOUS work, HITL control plane.
#   - WORK changes (code, data, docs) are AUTONOMOUS. With
#     required_approving_review_count = 0 (product profile — see
#     governance/CANONICAL-ORG-RULESET.md, the single source of truth), a PR
#     that touches NO owned path below merges on a GREEN gate with no human. The
#     gate is the control — so invest in it (coverage + mutation + fitness + Sonar)
#     and keep it deterministic. "Green" must be trustworthy because nothing else
#     gates work.
#   - CONTROL-PLANE changes — the gate's OWN definition — are HITL. With
#     require_code_owner_review = true, a PR touching an owned path needs a human
#     maintainer's approval. This is what keeps "green" honest: an agent must never
#     be able to weaken the gate that gates it.
#
# Replace @OWNER with the repo's HUMAN owning team (e.g. @three-cubes/maintainers).
# Agent App identities are deliberately NOT members and NOT repo admins, so they
# can neither self-approve a control-plane change nor bypass the rules.
#
# NOTE: there is deliberately NO `* @OWNER` line — a default owner would force
# review on EVERY PR (the admin-merge-spam failure mode). Own only the control
# plane. Repos extend this with their own gate-defining paths (e.g. schemas).

# ── CI / CD / automation (defines how things build, test, and merge) ─────────
/.github/                    @OWNER
/CODEOWNERS                  @OWNER
/.github/CODEOWNERS          @OWNER

# ── The gate's definition (what "green" means) ───────────────────────────────
/pyproject.toml              @OWNER   # [tool.tc_fitness] gate config + dependency pins
/.tc-fitness.toml            @OWNER
/uv.lock                     @OWNER
/scripts/                    @OWNER   # validators / generators the gate runs
/sonar-project.properties    @OWNER
/.pre-commit-config.yaml     @OWNER
/renovate.json               @OWNER
/.github/dependabot.yml      @OWNER
/.gitattributes              @OWNER
# Schemas define "valid" → repos that carry them own them here, e.g.:
#   /core/schemas/             @OWNER

# ── Security / governance / provenance ───────────────────────────────────────
/SECURITY.md                 @OWNER
/.secrets.baseline           @OWNER
/LICENSE                     @OWNER
/docs/adr/                   @OWNER
